A Grave  
(1916)  
  
    The path leads to  
    the dark arise where  
    toucans gather,  
    resonant, in the trees,  
    where elms add shadow  
    to the cerulean hue,  
    where the lost  
    grow up like dreams,  
    while the morning sky  
    unwinds.  


- Marianne Moore
